# Project Time & Financial Dashboard â€“ Power BI

## Overview
This dashboard provides a comprehensive view of project performance by combining **timesheet data** and **financial data**. It enables real-time tracking of project profitability, resource utilization, and cost efficiency.

The dashboard simulates how businesses can make informed decisions by integrating labor effort with budgetary insights.

---

##  Tools & Skills Demonstrated
- **Power BI Desktop**
- **Data Modeling (Relationships)**
- **DAX Calculated Measures**
- **KPI Cards, Donut & Bar Charts**
- **Slicers, Drill-throughs, and Filters**

---

## Data Sources
Two mock datasets were used to simulate a real-world business scenario:

### 1. Timesheet Data
| Column         | Description                              |
|----------------|------------------------------------------|
| Project ID     | Unique project reference                 |
| Employee       | Employee name                            |
| Role           | Role in the project                      |
| Date           | Date of work                             |
| Hours Worked   | Number of hours logged                   |
| Billable       | Whether the hours are client billable    |

### 2. Financial Data
| Column         | Description                              |
|----------------|------------------------------------------|
| Project ID     | Unique project reference                 |
| Client         | Name of the client                       |
| Start Date     | Project start date                       |
| End Date       | Project end date                         |
| Budget         | Project budget                           |
| Revenue        | Expected project revenue                 |
| Cost (to date) | Cost accrued so far                      |

---

##  Key Features of the Dashboard

### ðŸ”¹ KPIs
- **Total Hours Worked**
- **Billable vs Non-Billable Breakdown**
- **Utilization Rate**
- **Gross Margin %**
- **Revenue vs Actual Cost vs Budget**

###  Visuals
- Donut chart for time classification
- Clustered bar chart for revenue/cost comparison
- Table view of employee activity
- Drill-down filters by role, project, client

---

##  Insights Derived
- Identified **projects with highest cost overruns**
- Tracked **billable utilization by role and employee**
- Revealed **margin differences across clients**
- Supported **project managers in optimizing labor allocation**

